&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/judgment/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/judgment/> ;
  schema:name "Judgment" ;
  schema:description "A Judgment is a four-tuple (Z, I, f, α) — a conferred zone Z delimiting the officer's authorized action-space, an operative intent I = (E, ρ, T, R) specifying what purpose governs action within the zone, a situation f describing current conditions, and a chosen action α selected from Z ∩ R(f). The defining invariants: zone legitimacy (α ∈ Z, else excess of jurisdiction), intent-satisfaction (α ∈ R(f), else abuse of discretion), non-determinism (Z ∩ R(f) contains multiple candidates, else the act is calculation not judgment), and situation-responsiveness (α tracks f). Judgment is the act by which an officer bridges from intent and situation to specific action. Aristotle's phronesis is the philosophical ground: the capacity to identify the right particular act in the particular situation, irreducible to rule-following." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/> ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/judgment/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Intent, Friction, Mandate, Duty, Authority, Charter, HohfeldianPosition, NormativeSystem, Endeavor, Person, Office" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/judgment/> .

